		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				What was your feeling when you swore to your first patron?  <br>  <br>   <span style="font-weight:bold;"> Awe, and a sense of belonging.  I swore to him, over a year ago, when I started playing.  I had played for about 4 hours, before being introduced to, and swearing to him.  I was level 3.  He taught me  almost everything about the game, and took me under his wing.  He's still my patron, and I feel that we're very close.  He's very patient, and very very generous.  I'm proud to be his girl and I know, that I wouldn't still be in the game if it weren't in large part, for him.  We left our old alleg. together, a small crew of us, and the group of us are still close.  Our tiny branch of the group, my patron, grandpatron, and his former patron, are all still good friends. </span> <br>  <br> What did you think of your allegiance meetings (if any?)  <br>  <br>  <span style="font-weight:bold;">They have them quite frequently, and they get stuff accomplished, I assume.  I have a patchy schedule, and I miss them all.</span> <br>  <br> How are quests and communication organized?  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;">We have active message boards, and a calendar.  People talk a lot, and we have a council that schedules quests.  Our Allegiance loves questing, and we try to go on as many as possible.  There's something going on every day, and one or two big ones, a week.  Our queen, Cepolgara, announces what's going on over the alleg channel, and uses the motd to let us know what's going on.</span> <br>  <br> Did the release of mansions have any affect on your allegiance?  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;"> I don't know, as I wasn't around, pre-housing.  I would assume that it was very positively affected, because we're always hanging at the mansion.  It's the place to go, to meet up, socialize, prepare for quests, trade, all that.</span> <br>  <br> Was/Is your allegaince more chain or family oriented? <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;"> I'll say honestly, that when we joined this group, it was under a different monarch.  In my opinion, it was much more laid back, and more family oriented, back then. The group was smaller, and it seemed like everyone knew each other.  It was an honor guild, and there were rules against macros, chaining, and griefing.  There were no bots, either. <br>  <br> We still have rules in place against macroing and griefing, though there is use of rank chains.  We also have portal and  buff bots.  We are still an honor guild, and the majority of the members are kind, and honorable, but we're growing every day.     <br>  <br> It's hard to maintain that tight knit family feel, when ya don't recognize anyone, hanging on the mansion's front porch.  Our little group is still close as ever, though. <br>  <br> I belong to the Mithril Knights, on Wintersebb, under our good queen Cepolgara, who is incredibly kind, and exhibits great courage, patience, and generosity.  I am the proud vassal of Bruce the Darkknight, and the even prouder patron of Alden the Bold (my brother, irl). I complain about change, and progress, and growth, but I wouldn't have it any other way.  I love my alleg. </span> <br>  <br>  <br> 
