				What was your feeling when you swore to your first patron?  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;">It felt like I was joining a band of brothers. We had all been hanging around Holtburg for the past few days at the beginning of retail. So we were all quite aware of each other. My current patron and our group started out much the same. I met my group of co-vassals/patron on a quest and we just clicked. We were all either under someone else or like me, had just lost a patron to a server move. It just made sense to be in the same monarchy so we could communicate better. So we all joined under one of the group, whom I beleive was either already or his patron was about to join our current allegience. All I know is, we picked a good one!!</span> <br>  <br> What did you think of your allegiance meetings (if any?)  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;">In my current allegience today, we have them at times I haven't been able to visit. <br> How are quests and communication organized?  <br> Via a huge organized calender that is tightly run by anyone that is willing to organize a quest.</span> <br>  <br> Did the release of mansions have any affect on your allegiance?  <br>  <br> <span style="font-weight:bold;">The 1sttime I  joinedthis monarchy, Super Helix was at the helm, and Mansions were not invented yet. When I joined it again under Mehmet II we had one for sure, and it has continued to be maintained by Mark-Wheen just fine. For me being in the group a 2nd time, it seemed a bit more close sinceI know that at most times that I get to play, there is always something going on outta that place.</span> <br>  <br> Was/Is your allegaince more chain or family oriented? <span style="font-weight:bold;">Family Oriented definately. We do have a chain if those wish to join in it, but I'm not sure there are a whole lot of people in it. People justdon't come to our allegience for that, they come for the excellent people that make up this allegience.  <br>  <br>  <br> Iminthe Chosen Onez of Frostfell, headed by Mark-Wheen. My patron is Quazar'TheBrave' and our group consists of the coolest co-vassals Mr Magex II and the currently missing Wannabe. I've never really asked about my co-vassals vassals, if they have very many, but they all know we will help anyone from the allegience out. As for me I am down to one excellent vassal left, tyn and his inhouse allegience. I'm hoping that some of my older vassals that joined AC2 will once again come back and join me, so that we may once again have some major fun!! <br> </span>
