			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				My patron/Monarch is the same one I swore to the first day I played.  I also swore AT her hehe..  I had known my patron on the zone  for years. Her and another zone friend tried to convince me to play Asheron's Call.  I finally gave in and played.  What I did not know was I needed to update my video drivers.  I did fine in the game for about 30 minutes, then could not see a blasted thing.  I was running from Nanto to Mayoi when the darkness fell.  I kept running into rocks with orange dots nipping at my heals.  Thank goodness my monarch had heal other 2 learned!!!  My monarch kept laughing at me because I could not see the road. Or how to fight, heck I didn't know what dove mode was.  I think that was when I used a few choice lady-like words. <br>  <br> My monarchy is definately family oriented, in fact we have many people who play that are husband and wife in real life.  Real life always comes first.  No apologizes allowed for not being able to log on. <br>  <br> We also have an extended family.  Our extended family consists of other monarchy's that band together to do quests.  Some are set in stone and are done every week.  Others are done on a as requested basis.  We use a web board to keep up with each other.  We feel no need for organized meetings.  If there is a problem.. we take care of it.  It has worked since the game came out and I see no reason we would change it. <br>  <br> Since we have &quot;The Thunder Down Under&quot; (Quite a few members from New Zealand)  We have quests set up just about everyday at some real odd times. <br>  <br> As far as mansions go.... I love having the mansion, but I do not see as many people there as when we used &quot;Mule Mountain&quot; <br>  <br> Because of the extended family the monarchy has, we all used the same Mule area, every person was trustworthy who used that mountain.  Even if you were in our Monarchy, you were not shown where Mule Mountain was until we were all sure you could be trusted.  Someone was ALWAYS there.  We have many pictures on our site of that mountain doing crazy antics.  With so many monarchys using the same place to mule, many inpromptu quests happened.  Mule Mountain is still used as a meeting place for quests and such.  And it is still a beautiful place to sit back and chat with friends. <br>  <br> The release of the mansion did not change the way our allegiance operates.  But it did make us wish our friends list was much larger than it is now to accodate our extended family. <br>  <br> I am proud to be in Tabu's Monarchy.  She is a patron who has played since the start.  And still is playing her main toon daily.  There are not many of those kind of Monarchs around.   <br>  <br> I am amazed when I read trade boards.  I cannot believe the prices things go for.  In my monarchy, you ask if anyone needs it before you would even think of trading or selling it.  I am proud to say every member of our allegiance has a cottage or Villa.  Some just an apartment, but that is by their choice. <br>  <br> When housing would be released, not only would our fingers be typing to the bone, but the phones rang round the world for people to log on.  The packrats of the world became heros.  And thus, we all have housing, the same happens for body recoveries, quests, anything that someone needs help with.   <br>  <br> All in all, I love the Allegiance system. And my patron/monarch.  She is a very dear friend.  As are so many others I have met in the game. <br>  <br> Dodie/Tuesday <br> Leafcull <br> 		

