				What was your feeling when you swore to your first patron? <br>  <br> My first patron was my boyfriend. It only made sense to do it. His patron was a friend of his who brought us into Silver Citadel. They were nice enough as a group, but his patron never played. Eventually we broke from Silver Cit and swore into Butterfly Golem. It was the best choice we've made. BFG is great, we see our monarch and patron on all the time. And we're all definatly a family. <br>  <br>  <br> What did you think of your allegiance meetings (if any?) <br>  <br> We rarely have &quot;official&quot; meetings. We all are always running into each other in town and we all chat non-stop in game, so we're always up on what's going on. We also get up to date on things during quests. Everything is very informal and based on respect. <br>  <br> How are quests and communication organized? <br>  <br> Quests tend to be very organized if we remain within our group or with trusted members of sister allegiances. If my patron or our monarch leads them, they go very well. No one is left behind and everyone covers each other. It's done together or not at all. <br>  <br>   <br> Did the release of mansions have any affect on your allegiance?  <br>  <br> I was not around for the release of mansions.  <br>  <br>  <br> Personally, I think I'm pretty damn lucky to have stumbled across BFG. Silver Cit, while they seemed like nice people for the most part, were way too big of a group for my tastes. With BFG, I've got a great patron who will do anything for me and I am never wanting for anything. And vice versa. We all do what we can for each other. It's really very nice.
						<p><span class="SignatureTitle">-----signature-----</span>
						<div class="SignatureText">
						It's all fun and games, until I poke you in the eye. <br> Two wrongs don't make a right, <br> but three lefts do. <br> 
						</div>
							

			</td>
		</tr>
